    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix E1AP Setup Request optional field handling\n\n### Summary\nThe `createE1inst` function in `e1ap_common.c` was performing a shallow copy of the E1 Setup Request structure, leading to dangling pointers for optional fields like `gNB_cu_up_name`. This caused downstream functions to access invalid memory when processing these optional fields.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair2/E1AP/e1ap_common.c`: Replaced shallow copy with deep copy in `createE1inst` function to properly handle optional fields\n\n### Reproduction\nUnder certain network conditions, the CU-UP E1 Setup Request fails with a segmentation fault when accessing the `gNB_cu_up_name` field. This occurs because the field contains a dangling pointer after the original setup request memory is freed.\n\nThe issue can be reproduced by:\n1. Starting a CU-UP instance with a configured gNB name\n2. Establishing an E1 connection\n3. Observing a segfault when the CU-CP processes the Setup Request\n\nMemory analysis shows the `gNB_cu_up_name` pointer references freed memory, indicating the shallow copy issue in `createE1inst`.\n"
}